  "upgrade_suggestion": "2025 standard repress is the most accessible current-press option for this title; sonic alternatives are the original 2015 EU pressing (r7532352, harder to find) for source-cut purity, or the parallel 2025 Red Translucent Limited Edition (r33111807, same cut, color/artwork variant only).",
  "commentary": "Released September 2015, *Honeymoon* is Lana Del Rey's fourth studio album and the most stylistically consistent of her early-to-middle period — slow, orchestral, languid, with a deliberate avoidance of the radio-friendly hooks that anchored *Born to Die* and *Ultraviolence*. Del Rey co-produced with Rick Nowels and Kieron Menzies (the *Ultraviolence* team minus Dan Auerbach), and the album was recorded primarily at The Green Building in Santa Monica.\n\nThe aesthetic is intentional: Del Rey has described *Honeymoon* as her \"most cinematic\" record, and the arrangements lean into film-noir strings, woozy reverb, and tempos that rarely break out of ballad territory. *High by the Beach* is the most up-tempo moment; the rest of the album sits in *Music to Watch Boys To* / *Terrence Loves You* / *Salvatore* mode — jazz-influenced, slow-burning, deliberately patient. The album includes a spoken-word reading of T.S. Eliot's *Burnt Norton* as track 6, which is either pretentious or perfect depending on how you feel about that kind of thing.\n\nCritical reception was strong but quieter than her earlier records — *Honeymoon* is the album most often cited by Lana fans as \"the one that grew on me.\" It's also the last fully Nowels-and-Menzies-produced Del Rey album before Jack Antonoff entered the picture for *Norman Fucking Rockwell!* — making the production lineage in this collection (Nowels/Menzies on *Honeymoon*, Antonoff on *NFR!*) trace the actual hinge of her career.\n\n**About this 2025 USA & Europe repress (2×LP):** catalog `4750764`, barcode `00602547488275`. The deadwax shows `171758E1`–`171758E4` cut codes (one per side) — Universal/Polydor's reissue cutting from the original 2015 source. The `1713519` / `1712205` / `1751205` / `1713360` numbers are Universal's job/cut tracking codes from the 2025 repress run. This is a black 2LP standard issue; the parallel Limited Edition (r33111807) was issued the same year on Red Translucent vinyl with alternative artwork.\n\nThe standard 2025 repress is the cleanest current-press option for *Honeymoon* on vinyl — original 2015 EU pressings (r7532352) are also good if you find them, but the 2025 cut is the more accessible current option.\n\n### Gemini Notes\n\nReleased in 2015, *Honeymoon* is Lana Del Rey's fourth studio album. It marked a return to the cinematic, baroque pop of her debut, featuring lush string arrangements, jazzy undertones, and themes of doomed romance and Californian melancholy.\n\n**About this pressing:**",
